<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>HALLMARK: Citation Hallucination Benchmark — Research Agora</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
    <script>(function(){var t=localStorage.getItem('theme')||'dark';document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme',t)})();</script>
    <style>
        .hallmark-overview {
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }
        .hallmark-overview p {
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            line-height: 1.7;
        }
        .hallmark-overview h3 {
            font-size: 1.15rem;
            margin-top: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
        .hallmark-overview ul {
            padding-left: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }
        .hallmark-overview li {
            margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .hallmark-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr));
            gap: 1rem;
            margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
        }
        .hallmark-stat {
            background: var(--bg-secondary);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: var(--radius);
            padding: 1rem;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .hallmark-stat .stat-value {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: var(--primary);
        }
        .hallmark-stat .stat-label {
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            color: var(--text-muted);
            margin-top: 0.25rem;
        }
        .tier-badges {
            display: flex;
            gap: 0.5rem;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            margin: 0.5rem 0;
        }
        .badge-easy { background: var(--green-light); color: var(--green); }
        .badge-medium { background: var(--yellow-light); color: var(--yellow); }
        .badge-hard { background: var(--red-light); color: var(--red); }
        .coming-soon {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 3rem 2rem;
            color: var(--text-muted);
            border: 2px dashed var(--border);
            border-radius: var(--radius);
            margin: 1.5rem 0;
        }
        .coming-soon h3 {
            font-size: 1.25rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            color: var(--text);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <nav class="site-nav">
        <div class="container nav-container">
            <a href="index.html" class="nav-brand">Research Agora</a>
            <div class="nav-links">
                <a href="index.html" class="nav-link">Skills</a>
                <a href="benchmarks.html" class="nav-link active">Benchmarks</a>
                <a href="docs.html" class="nav-link">Docs</a>
                <button class="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()" aria-label="Toggle dark/light mode" title="Toggle theme">
                    <span class="theme-icon">&#x2600;&#xFE0F;</span>
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <header>
        <div class="container">
            <h1>HALLMARK: Citation Hallucination Benchmark</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Measuring how well tools detect hallucinated citations in ML papers</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container" style="padding-top: 2rem;">
        <section class="hallmark-overview">
            <p>
                <strong>HALLMARK</strong> is a citation hallucination benchmark for evaluating reference-verification tools on ML papers.
                It provides <strong>2,525 annotated entries</strong> spanning <strong>14 hallucination types</strong> across <strong>3 difficulty tiers</strong>,
                with <strong>6 sub-tests per entry</strong> for fine-grained diagnosis.
            </p>

            <div class="hallmark-grid">
                <div class="hallmark-stat">
                    <div class="stat-value">2,525</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Annotated Entries</div>
                </div>
                <div class="hallmark-stat">
                    <div class="stat-value">14</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Hallucination Types</div>
                </div>
                <div class="hallmark-stat">
                    <div class="stat-value">3</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Difficulty Tiers</div>
                </div>
                <div class="hallmark-stat">
                    <div class="stat-value">6</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Sub-tests per Entry</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Difficulty Tiers</h3>
            <div class="tier-badges">
                <span class="badge badge-easy">Easy</span>
                <span class="badge badge-medium">Medium</span>
                <span class="badge badge-hard">Hard</span>
            </div>
            <p>
                Tiers reflect how difficult a hallucination is to detect: <strong>Easy</strong> entries have obvious errors (e.g., nonexistent DOIs),
                <strong>Medium</strong> entries require cross-referencing metadata, and <strong>Hard</strong> entries involve subtle misattributions
                that demand deep semantic understanding of the cited work.
            </p>

            <h3>Built-in Baselines</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>DOI-only</strong> &mdash; resolves DOIs and flags missing or broken links</li>
                <li><strong>bibtex-updater</strong> &mdash; metadata-based verification via BibTeX normalization</li>
                <li><strong>LLM-based</strong> &mdash; direct LLM prompting for citation plausibility</li>
                <li><strong>Ensemble</strong> &mdash; combines DOI + metadata + LLM signals</li>
                <li><strong>HaRC</strong> &mdash; hallucinated reference classification baseline</li>
                <li><strong>verify-citations</strong> &mdash; end-to-end citation verification pipeline</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Metrics</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Detection Rate</strong> &mdash; fraction of hallucinated citations correctly flagged</li>
                <li><strong>F1</strong> &mdash; harmonic mean of precision and recall</li>
                <li><strong>Tier-weighted F1</strong> &mdash; F1 weighted by difficulty tier (Hard counts more)</li>
                <li><strong>detect@k</strong> &mdash; detection rate within the top-k ranked citations</li>
                <li><strong>ECE</strong> &mdash; expected calibration error of confidence scores</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Final system rankings use <strong>Plackett&ndash;Luce ranking</strong> to aggregate across metrics and tiers into a single ordering.
            </p>

            <h3>Design Principles</h3>
            <p>
                HALLMARK draws on best practices from established code and ML benchmarks:
                <strong>HumanEval</strong> (functional correctness via test cases),
                <strong>SWE-bench</strong> (real-world task grounding),
                <strong>LiveCodeBench</strong> (contamination-resistant temporal splits),
                and <strong>ONEBench</strong> (multi-metric aggregation into a unified score).
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="benchmark-section">
            <div class="benchmark-header">
                <h2>Leaderboard</h2>
                <div class="benchmark-meta">
                    <span class="badge badge-formal">F1-H</span>
                    <span class="badge badge-plugin">dev_public</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            {% set hallmark_results = results | selectattr('benchmark-id', 'equalto', 'hallmark') | list %}
            {% if hallmark_results %}
            <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                Ranked by F1-Hallucination (primary metric) on <code>dev_public</code> split (1,119 entries).
                Arrows indicate preferred direction.
            </p>
            <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
            <table class="leaderboard">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>#</th>
                        <th>Baseline</th>
                        <th>Type</th>
                        <th>DR &uarr;</th>
                        <th>F1-H &uarr;</th>
                        <th>TW-F1 &uarr;</th>
                        <th>FPR &darr;</th>
                        <th>ECE &darr;</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    {% for entry in hallmark_results %}
                    <tr>
                        <td>{{ loop.index }}</td>
                        <td><strong>{{ entry.skill }}</strong></td>
                        <td><span class="badge {% if entry.model == 'llm' %}badge-formal{% else %}badge-heuristic{% endif %}">{{ entry.model | upper }}</span></td>
                        <td>{{ "%.3f" | format(entry.metrics.detection_rate) }}</td>
                        <td><strong>{{ "%.3f" | format(entry.metrics.f1_hallucination) }}</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ "%.3f" | format(entry.metrics.tier_weighted_f1) }}</td>
                        <td>{{ "%.3f" | format(entry.metrics.fpr) }}</td>
                        <td>{% if entry.metrics.ece is not none %}{{ "%.3f" | format(entry.metrics.ece) }}{% else %}&mdash;{% endif %}</td>
                    </tr>
                    {% endfor %}
                </tbody>
            </table>
            </div>
            {% else %}
            <div class="coming-soon">
                <h3>No Results Yet</h3>
                <p>Submit results following the <a href="https://github.com/rpatrik96/research-agora/blob/main/registry/BENCHMARKS.md">submission guidelines</a>.</p>
            </div>
            {% endif %}
        </section>

        {# Dynamic rendering for any additional registered benchmarks (skip hallmark — shown above) #}
        {% for benchmark in benchmarks if benchmark.id != 'hallmark' %}
        <section class="benchmark-section">
            <div class="benchmark-header">
                <h2>{{ benchmark.name }}</h2>
                <div class="benchmark-meta">
                    <span class="badge badge-formal">{{ benchmark['primary-metric'] | upper }}</span>
                    <span class="badge badge-plugin">{{ benchmark['refresh-cadence'] }} refresh</span>
                    <a href="{{ benchmark.homepage }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="source-link">Repository</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p>{{ benchmark.description }}</p>
            <p><strong>Task:</strong> {{ benchmark.task }}</p>

            <div class="benchmark-tags">
                {% for tag in benchmark.tags %}
                <span class="badge badge-type">{{ tag }}</span>
                {% endfor %}
            </div>

            {% set bench_results = results | selectattr('benchmark-id', 'equalto', benchmark.id) | list %}
            {% if bench_results %}
            <h3>Leaderboard</h3>
            <table class="leaderboard">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>#</th>
                        <th>Skill</th>
                        <th>Model</th>
                        {% for metric in benchmark.metrics %}
                        <th>{{ metric | upper }}</th>
                        {% endfor %}
                        <th>Date</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    {% for entry in bench_results %}
                    <tr>
                        <td>{{ loop.index }}</td>
                        <td><code>{{ entry.skill }}</code></td>
                        <td><span class="badge {{ entry.model | model_badge }}">{{ entry.model }}</span></td>
                        {% for metric in benchmark.metrics %}
                        <td>{{ "%.3f" | format(entry.metrics.get(metric, 0)) }}</td>
                        {% endfor %}
                        <td>{{ entry.date }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    {% endfor %}
                </tbody>
            </table>
            {% else %}
            <div class="empty-leaderboard">
                <p>No results submitted yet. Be the first!</p>
                <p>See <a href="https://github.com/rpatrik96/research-agora/blob/main/registry/BENCHMARKS.md">submission guidelines</a>.</p>
            </div>
            {% endif %}

            <details>
                <summary>Relevant Skills</summary>
                <div class="relevant-skills">
                    {% for skill_name in benchmark['relevant-skills'] %}
                    <code>/plugin install {{ skill_name }}@research-agora</code>
                    {% endfor %}
                </div>
            </details>
        </section>
        {% endfor %}
    </main>

    <footer class="container">
        <p>
            <a href="https://github.com/rpatrik96/research-agora">GitHub</a> |
            <a href="https://github.com/rpatrik96/research-agora/blob/main/registry/BENCHMARKS.md">Submit Results</a> |
            <a href="https://github.com/rpatrik96/research-agora/blob/main/INTEROP.md">Interop</a> |
            <a href="https://github.com/rpatrik96/research-agora/blob/main/PLATFORM.md">Platform Design</a>
        </p>
        <p class="generated">Generated {{ generated }}</p>
    </footer>
    <script src="theme.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
